RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s Foreign Minister Prince Faisal bin Farhan received a phone call from his British counterpart Liz Truss, the Kingdom’s foreign ministry said on Thursday.
During the call, they reviewed bilateral relations and ways to enhance them, in addition to discussing regional and international developments.
Following the call, Truss said: “The UK is committed to working with international partners to call out Russia’s egregious use of violence in Ukraine and to support the humanitarian response.” Spoke to Saudi Arabia’s @FaisalbinFarhan. The UK is committed to working with international partners to call out Russia’s egregious use of violence in Ukraine and to support the humanitarian response. It is vital that the @UN speaks with one voice. pic.twitter.com/7vU4ZB9dbz — Liz Truss (@trussliz) March 23, 2022 